r%20of%20doom%20for%20a%20lot%20of%20people.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20conundrum%20is%20becoming%20familiar%20to%20an%20increasing%20number%20of%20workers.%20As%20companies%20race%20to%20adopt%20AI%20and%20boost%20efficiency%2C%20people%20are%20being%20asked%20to%20build%2C%20use%2C%20and%20deploy%20tools%20they%20suspect%20are%20meant%20to%20replace%20their%20coworkers%2C%20peers%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbuilt-ai-agent-job-boss-replacement-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eor%20even%20themselves%3C%2Fa%3E.%20While%20the%20higher-ups%20say%20their%20AI%20strategy%20is%20meant%20to%20enhance%20their%20workforce%2C%20employees%20often%20aren't%20so%20sure.%20The%20result%20is%20a%20quiet%20but%20mounting%20tension%20in%20which%20doing%20your%20job%20may%20help%20eliminate%20someone%20else's.%20People%20are%20becoming%20inadvertent%20job%20executioners.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPressberg%20says%20he%20still%20hasn't%20decided%20what%20he's%20going%20to%20do%20about%20his%20ethical%20dilemma.%20It's%20not%20like%20he%20has%20close%20working%20relationships%20with%20the%20people%20who%20would%20be%20on%20the%20way%20out%20the%20door%2C%20and%20he%20figures%20he's%20not%20the%20only%20person%20who's%20making%20this%20type%20of%20product.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20can%20kind%20of%20ride%20the%20horse%20or%20get%20trampled%20by%20the%20horse%2C%20but%20I%20don't%20know%20if%20you%20can%20just%20sit%20back%20and%20watch%20the%20horse%20race%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20is%20the%20most%20fraught%20workplace%20issue%20of%20the%20moment.%20Predictions%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feconomists-business-leaderss-react-citrini-report-ai-recession-stock-crash-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI-driven%20recessions%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgodfather-of-ai-geoffrey-hinton-2026-job-losses-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emassive%20job%20losses%3C%2Fa%3E%20abound.%20People%20are%20being%20bombarded%20by%20a%20slew%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flist-companies-replacing-human-employees-with-ai-layoffs-workforce-reductions%23wisetech-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI-related%20layoff%20announcements%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20high-profile%20companies%20such%20as%20Snap%2C%20Block%2C%20Meta%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcoinbase-layoffs-ai-brian-armstrong-job-cuts-letter-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eand%20Coinbase%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Even%20the%20economists%20and%20tech%20executives%20who%20take%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-job-losses-dot-com-bubble-internet-economy-morgan-stanley-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoptimistic%20view%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20AI's%20effects%20acknowledge%20that%20some%20level%20of%20workforce%20disruption%20is%20inevitable.%20Goldman%20Sachs%20economists%20say%20AI%20is%20already%20a%20modest%20net%20drag%20on%20the%20labor%20market%2C%20and%20Morgan%20Stanley%20analysts%20estimate%20that%20firms%20adopting%20AI%20have%20cut%20headcount%20by%204%25%2C%20though%20that's%20accompanied%20by%20an%2011.5%25%20gain%20in%20productivity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20helps%20to%20explain%20why%20corporate%20messaging%20around%20AI%20use%20has%20become%20harsher.%20Whereas%20a%20year%20or%20two%20ago%2C%20executives%20were%20encouraging%20employees%20to%20experiment%20with%20the%20technology%2C%20many%20businesses%20are%20now%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-google-jpmorgan-make-ai-performance-reviews-goals-raises-promotions-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etracking%20AI%20use%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20figuring%20it%20into%20performance%20reviews%20and%20promotion%20decisions.%20The%20vibe%20has%20gone%20from%20%26quot%3Btinker%20around%26quot%3B%20to%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmanagers-are-in-charge-of-making-you-use-ai-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ejust%20do%20it%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%20Shareholders%20expect%20payoffs%20now%2C%20not%20in%20some%20nebulous%20distant%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20some%2C%20the%20transition%20from%20builder%20to%20hangman%20is%2C%20at%20most%2C%20a%20moral%20speedbump%20on%20the%20road%20to%20untapped%20efficiencies%20and%20major%20profits.%20That's%20the%20case%20for%20British%20serial%20entrepreneur%20James%20Buckley-Thorp.%20He%20founded%20his%20latest%20project%2C%20construction%20insurance%20platform%20Atlian.ai%2C%20with%20the%20explicit%20goal%20of%20cutting%20half%20a%20dozen%20steps%20and%20people%20%E2%80%94%20analysts%2C%20surveyors%2C%20copywriters%20%E2%80%94%20out%20of%20the%20process%20for%20producing%20insurance%20broker%20quotes%20for%20building%20projects.%20Buckley-Thorp%2C%20whose%20previous%20venture%20was%20in%20life%20insurance%2C%20says%20a%20VC%20was%20upfront%20when%20they%20asked%3A%20%26quot%3BCan%20you%20basically%20reduce%20the%20workforce%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe's%20excited%20about%20the%20potential%20benefits%20for%20customers%2C%20who%20he%20believes%20will%20be%20able%20to%20use%20his%20platform%20to%20obtain%20and%20compare%20insurance%20quotes%20in%20a%20matter%20of%20days%20instead%20of%20weeks.%20He%20hopes%20brokers%20will%20pass%20savings%20they've%20gotten%20by%20cutting%20so%20many%20people%20out%20of%20the%20process%20onto%20builders%2C%20and%20that%20timelines%20for%20major%20construction%20projects%20will%20speed%20up.%20As%20for%20the%20people%20whose%20work%20he's%20attempting%20to%20nix%2C%20that's%20just%20the%20name%20of%20the%20game.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20developing%20this%20with%20a%20VC%2C%20and%20community%2C%20morality%20questions%20are%20usually%20an%20afterthought.%20That%20sounds%20very%20brutal%2C%20but%20there%20is%20so%20much%20waste%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BThere%20is%20a%20massive%20workforce%20behind%20that%20that%20would%20suffer%2C%20but%20you've%20got%20to%20adapt%20or%20die.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20some%20level%20of%20comfort%20that%20comes%20with%20being%20the%20one%20who%20is%20swinging%20the%20ax.%20You%20know%20you%20have%20your%20grip%20on%20the%20handle%20and%20are%20making%20the%20choice.%20What%20can%20be%20more%20disquieting%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsoftware-engineers-lessons-white-collar-works-ai-disruption-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ewatching%20the%20ax%20swing%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20wondering%20whether%20you%20accidentally%20helped%20forge%20the%20blade.%20I%20recently%20caught%20up%20with%20a%20friend%20who's%20been%20pretty%20all%20in%20on%20AI%20at%20their%20startup%20job%2C%20until%20the%20asks%20started%20to%20feel%20specifically%20geared%20toward%20wiping%20out%20the%20teams%20they%20work%20with%20closely.%20They've%20started%20to%20wonder%20if%20it's%20time%20to%20look%20for%20another%20job.%20I%20heard%20from%20someone%20while%20reporting%20this%20story%20about%20a%20sort%20of%20workplace%20survivor's%20guilt%20%E2%80%94%20only%20after%20two%20of%20their%20colleagues%20were%20laid%20off%20did%20they%20realize%20that%20all%20the%20AI%20adoption%20they%20were%20helping%20their%20bosses%20with%20was%20a%20factor.%20%26quot%3BIn%20hindsight%2C%20it's%20pretty%20evident%20that%20it%20was%20a%20major%20factor%20for%20the%20decision%2C%20especially%20because%20incorporating%20it%20early%20and%20aggressively%20made%20me%20sort%20of%20the%20AI%20expert%20on%20the%20team%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20dynamics%20aren't%20necessarily%20new%20at%20work.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmiddle-managers-rto-gen-z-navigate-office-return-tensions-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMiddle%20managers%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20long%20been%20given%20the%20ugly%20job%20of%20deciding%20who%20goes%20amid%20layoffs%2C%20and%20it's%20not%20unheard%20of%20for%20employees%20to%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-employee-ai-adoption-non-technical-software-engineer-performance-review-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Egiven%20a%20mandate%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20make%20things%20more%20efficient%20so%20that%20fewer%20people%20are%20needed.%20The%20difference%20with%20AI%20is%20how%20this%20responsibility%20is%20being%20dispersed%20to%20a%20broader%20set%20of%20workers.%20While%20a%20startup%20founder%20or%20executive%20may%20see%20an%20enormous%20money-making%20opportunity%20in%20leveraging%20AI%2C%20rank-and-file%20employees%20are%20weighing%20whether%20their%20AI%20tinkering%20is%20protecting%20their%20job%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdata-analyst-quit-job-over-concerns-ai-would-replace-them-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esowing%20the%20seeds%20of%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20larger%20layoff.%20The%20reward%20for%20going%20along%20isn't%20riches%2C%20it's%20staying%20off%20the%20unemployment%20rolls.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20a%20cognitive%20dissonance%20that%20arises%20when%20people%20are%20compelled%20to%20be%20self-protective%20in%20a%20way%20that%20feels%20corrosive%2C%20explains%20Constance%20Noonan%20Hadley%2C%20an%20organizational%20psychologist%20who%20founded%20the%20Institute%20for%20Life%20at%20Work%2C%20a%20think%20tank.%20That%20can%20be%20at%20least%20partly%20mitigated%20by%20ensuring%20the%20people%20doing%20the%20dirty%20work%20can%20see%20and%20understand%20why%20changes%20are%20necessary%20%E2%80%94%20the%20company%20is%20pivoting%20in%20an%20exciting%20new%20direction%20with%20a%20lot%20of%20buy-in%2C%20or%20they've%20sunsetted%20a%20project%20that's%20long%20been%20obviously%20defunct.%20What's%20tricky%20with%20AI%20is%20that%20there's%20a%20lot%20of%20uncertainty%20about%20what%20the%20gains%20will%20actually%20be.%20Does%20it%20make%20sense%20to%20wipe%20out%20the%20entire%20design%20team%20only%20to%20discover%20that%20ChatGPT%20images%20are%20not%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20good%20enough%20to%20win%20over%20customers%3F%20There's%20also%20the%20question%20of%20whether%20potential%20gains%20are%20worth%20it%20on%20balance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAre%20we%20getting%20to%20the%20point%20where%20everyone%20wants%20to%20have%20a%20five-person%20company%20so%20that%20there%20is%20massive%20unemployment%20for%20the%20sake%20of%20increasing%20and%20increasing%20profitability%3F%26quot%3B%20Hadley%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMuch%20of%20the%20solution%20to%20this%20is%20about%20communication%20%E2%80%94%20execs%20making%20sure%20employees%20understand%20the%20AI%20roadmap%20and%20the%20decisions%20being%20made%20around%20it.%20More%20senior%20employees%2C%20who%20have%20more%20visibility%2C%20are%20likelier%20to%20feel%20better%20about%20what's%20going%20on%20and%20their%20own%20complicity%20than%20junior%20employees%20who%20are%20more%20in%20the%20dark.%20A%20recent%20Gallup%20poll%20found%20that%2067%25%20of%20executive%20leaders%20are%20frequent%20AI%20users%2C%20compared%20to%2046%25%20of%20individual%20contributors.%20A%202025%20survey%20from%20Columbia%20Business%20School%20found%20that%2076%25%20of%20executives%20reported%20that%20their%20employees%20were%20enthusiastic%20about%20AI%20adoption%20at%20their%20organizations%2C%20but%20only%2031%25%20of%20individual%20contributors%20actually%20felt%20good%20about%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20also%20important%20for%20firms%20to%20lay%20out%20how%20to%20actually%20use%20AI%2C%20and%20what%20is%20useful%20vs.%20superficial.%20Research%20from%20the%20Stanford%20Social%20Media%20Lab%20and%20BetterUp%2C%20a%20professional%20training%20and%20coaching%20company%2C%20found%20that%2040%25%20of%20American%20deskworkers%20believe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworkslop-oozing-americas-white-collar-offices-generative-ai-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethey've%20received%20%26quot%3Bworkslop%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20a%20colleague%2C%20meaning%20stuff%20thoughtlessly%20shot%20out%20by%20AI.%20Kate%20Niederhoffer%2C%20a%20social%20psychologist%20and%20the%20chief%20scientist%20at%20BetterUp%20says%20that%20just%20cranking%20out%20any%20old%20email%20with%20AI%20is%20%26quot%3Ba%20very%20compelling%20path%20of%20least%20resistance%26quot%3B%20when%20you're%20expected%20to%20use%20the%20tools%20or%20%26quot%3Btrying%20to%20do%20more%20with%20less%26quot%3B%20and%20everything%20is%20treated%20as%20urgent.%20But%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Femployees-workload-increasing-ai-workslop-ey-work-reimagined-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esending%20around%20workslop%3C%2Fa%3E%20makes%20people%20more%20annoyed%20with%20and%20confused%20by%20one%20another.%20And%20when%20you%20participate%2C%20your%20coworkers%20see%20you%20as%20less%20creative%2C%20capable%2C%20reliable%2C%20and%20smart.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmy%20Gallo%2C%20a%20workplace%20consultant%2C%20tells%20me%20she%20sees%20a%20sort%20of%20%26quot%3Bsinking%20suspicion%26quot%3B%20around%20AI%20among%20her%20clients%2C%20an%20attitude%20of%20%26quot%3Byes%2C%20this%20is%20really%20helpful%2C%20I'm%20glad%20I'm%20using%20it%E2%80%A6%20and%20this%20is%20really%20concerning.%26quot%3B%20People%20question%20whether%20they%20should%20build%20and%20use%20AI%20tools%20as%20effectively%20as%20possible%20to%20try%20to%20protect%20themselves%2C%20which%20is%20a%20hard%20issue%20to%20navigate%2C%20because%20%26quot%3Byou%20don't%20want%20to%20tell%20someone%20to%20be%20intentionally%20bad%20at%20their%20job%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20AI%20becomes%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvalentines-date-ai-companion-wine-bar-cringe-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eintermediary%20in%20our%20relationships%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20we%20don't%20form%20more%20typical%20interpersonal%20connections%20with%20our%20managers%20and%20colleagues%2C%20making%20everything%20feel%20more%20distant%20at%20a%20moment%20when%20we%20should%20have%20more%20honest%20conversations%20about%20how%20things%20are%20going.%20Workers%20have%20long%20been%20asked%20to%20balance%20the%20demands%20of%20customers%2C%20consumers%2C%20coworkers%2C%20and%20shareholders.%20Everyone%20has%20to%20make%20choices%20about%20how%20comfortable%20they%20feel%20about%20the%20various%20tradeoffs.%20%26quot%3BAI%20has%20made%20it%20more%20immediate%2C%20which%20is%20like%2C%20'I%20could%20build%20this%20tool%20today%2C%20and%2020%20people%20could%20lose%20their%20jobs%20tomorrow%2C'%26quot%3B%20Gallo%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20just%20a%20threat%20to%20a%20paycheck%3B%20it's%20a%20threat%20to%20a%20career%20path%20and%20long-term%20corporate%20success.%20Many%20of%20the%20tasks%20that%20more%20senior%20employees%20are%20using%20AI%20to%20take%20care%20of%20are%20the%20basic%20blocking%20and%20tackling%20that%20junior%20employees%20have%20historically%20handled.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20even%20white-collar%20professional%20service%20industries%20deploy%20entry-level%20and%20even%20midlevel%20employees%20as%20order-takers%2C%20and%20AI%20can%20take%20orders%2C%26quot%3B%20Pressberg%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20problem%20is%2C%20if%20the%20strategizers%20never%20teach%20up-and-comers%20the%20tactics%20and%20instead%20automate%20them%20away%2C%20the%20bottom%20of%20the%20ladder%20gets%20cut%20off.%20There's%20no%20new%20crop%20of%20strategizers%2010%2C%2020%20years%20down%20the%20line%20who%20have%20developed%20the%20judgment%20and%20creativity%20that%20comes%20with%20repetitively%20doing%20something.%20This%20leaves%20a%20leadership%20vacuum%20at%20the%20top%20of%20the%20company.%20The%20veterans%20may%20have%20managed%20to%20hold%20onto%20their%20jobs%2C%20but%20they're%20headed%20for%20retirement%20and%20leaving%20a%20hollowed-out%20structure%20behind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20is%20an%20exciting%20tool%20for%20many%20workers%20and%20leaders%2C%20and%20it%20has%20a%20lot%20of%20realized%20and%20unrealized%20potential.%20Even%20for%20the%20skeptics%2C%20sitting%20it%20out%20completely%20probably%20isn't%20an%20option.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20diving%20in%20isn't%20a%20surefire%20way%20to%20protect%20yourself%20%E2%80%94%20many%20of%20the%20workers%20let%20go%20by%20Citi%20in%20its%20recent%20round%20of%20layoffs%20were%20reportedly%20part%20of%20its%20program%20for%20%26quot%3BAI%20Champions%20and%20Accelerators.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Femily-stewart%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEmily%20Stewart%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%2C%20writing%20about%20business%20and%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Femployees-building-ai-tools-help-bosses-employers-lay-off-coworkers-2026-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1778143081000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69fba4c13cfefc31768d6580%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Femployees-building-ai-tools-help-bosses-employers-lay-off-coworkers-2026-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Employees%20are%20worried%20that%20they're%20becoming%20accidental%20job%20executioners%3A%20By%20developing%20AI%20tools%2C%20their%20bosses%20can%20ax%20their%20coworkers%20%E2%80%94%20or%20themselves.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22estewart%40insider.com%20(Emily%20Stewart)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Bharat%20Forge%20Q4%20result%3A%20Profit%20falls%2017%25%20to%20%E2%82%B9233.4%20cr%2C%20revenue%20at%20%E2%82%B94%2C528%20cr%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1778142972000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.busi