now-covered%20trench.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69fc3852c9dd4cb81cda7f7c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUkrainian%20infantry%20soldiers%20from%20the%20156th%20Brigade%20train%20at%20a%20snow-covered%20training%20ground%20in%20Kharkiv.%3Cp%3EDiego%20Herrera%20Carcedo%2FAnadolu%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EUkraine%20is%20looking%20to%20draft%20a%20law%20by%20the%20end%20of%202026%20that%20will%20legalize%20postwar%20mercenary%20work.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt%20could%20help%20its%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20soldiers%20turn%20their%20battlefield%20experience%20into%20careers.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EUkraine%20is%20estimated%20to%20have%20880%2C000%20to%201%20million%20troops%2C%20or%20at%20least%206%25%20of%20its%20workforce.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine%20is%20moving%20to%20legalize%20private%20military%20companies%2C%20paving%20the%20way%20for%20its%20roughly%20900%2C000%20troops%20to%20potentially%20work%20as%20mercenaries%20in%20a%20postwar%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fzelenskyy-interview-putin-russia-ukraine-election-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EUkrainian%20President%20Volodymyr%20Zelenskyy%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20on%20Wednesday%20that%20he%20had%20instructed%20government%20officials%20and%20intelligence%20services%20to%20draft%20a%20law%20that%20would%20permit%20such%20organizations%20by%20the%20end%20of%202026.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20in%20his%20regular%20address%2C%20Zelenskyy%20said%20the%20decision%20was%20made%20as%20part%20of%20a%20discussion%20of%20%26quot%3Bpostwar%20opportunities%20for%20our%20warriors.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20whole%20world%20sees%20that%20the%20Ukrainian%20warrior%20is%20truly%20strong%20and%20truly%20experienced.%20Our%20security%20export%20%E2%80%94%20after%20this%20war%20and%20for%20veterans%20%E2%80%94%20must%20become%20a%20real%20business%20opportunity%2C%26quot%3B%20Zelenskyy%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine%20fields%20between%20880%2C000%20and%201%20million%20active%20personnel%2C%20a%20roughly%20fivefold%20increase%20from%20pre-war%20levels.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20country%20had%20about%20200%2C000%20troops%20and%20personnel%20in%20early%202022%2C%20before%20conducting%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-some-ukrainians-dodge-the-draft-escape-fighting-russias-invasion-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emass%20mobilization%20of%20men%3C%2Fa%3E%20aged%2027%20to%2060%20that%20year.%20In%202024%2C%20it%20lowered%20the%20draft%20age%20to%2025.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20million%20troops%20could%20represent%20at%20least%206%25%20of%20Ukraine's%20total%20workforce.%20Hundreds%20of%20thousands%20more%20adults%20now%20work%20for%20local%20defense%20industry%20manufacturers.%20Ukraine%20hasn't%20been%20publishing%20labor%20surveys%20since%202022%2C%20and%20it's%20difficult%20to%20estimate%20how%20many%20working%20adults%20it%20will%20have%20after%20the%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGovernment%20statistics%20from%202021%20said%20the%20country%20had%20a%20labor%20force%20of%2017.4%20million%20people%2C%20but%20millions%20of%20workers%20have%20since%20left%20or%20been%20displaced.%20It's%20unclear%20how%20many%20will%20return.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJobs%20are%20also%20hard%20to%20come%20by%2C%20with%20Ukrainian%20officials%20saying%20in%202024%20that%20the%20employment%20rate%20was%20around%2053%25.%20Postwar%20recovery%20often%20varies%20widely%20by%20country%2C%20but%20research%20shows%20that%20the%20longer%20a%20conflict%20drags%20on%2C%20the%20more%20likely%20that%20its%20economy%20takes%20more%20than%2010%20years%20to%20recover.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%202022%20analysis%20by%20the%20London-based%20think%20tank%20Centre%20for%20Economic%20Policy%20Research%2C%20for%20example%2C%20found%20that%20more%20than%20half%20of%20modern%20postwar%20economies%20took%20at%20least%20two%20decades%20to%20catch%20up%20to%20the%20GDP%20per%20capita%20growth%20of%20peer%20nations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine%20has%20been%20bolstered%20somewhat%20by%20foreign%20aid%20and%20a%20surging%20local%20defense%20industry%2C%20and%20its%20GDP%20has%20increased%20steadily%20by%20between%203%20to%205%25%20each%20year%20since%20plunging%2029.1%25%20when%20the%20war%20began.%20But%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-war-challenging-west-obsession-with-perfect-weapons-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efull-scale%20war%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20also%20already%20entered%20its%20fifth%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20law%20could%20thus%20be%20a%20significant%20boon%20for%20troops%20exiting%20the%20war%2C%20with%20skills%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-commander-drone-pilots-hit-russian-troops-close-range-madyar-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edrone%20piloting%20and%20maintenance%3C%2Fa%3E%20being%20increasingly%20in%20demand%20overseas.%20Kyiv%20said%20in%20January%20that%20it%20trained%20at%20least%2050%2C000%20drone%20pilots%20in%202025%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMercenary%20work%20is%20formally%20outlawed%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20though%20the%20country%20has%20relied%20heavily%20on%20volunteer%20organizations%20and%20battalions%20since%202022.%20Now%2C%20however%2C%20many%20informal%20fighting%20units%20have%20since%20been%20absorbed%20into%20Ukraine's%20official%20military%20structure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZelenskyy%20didn't%20say%20if%20Ukraine's%20government%20would%20be%20involved%20in%20regulating%20private%20military%20companies.%20Nor%20did%20he%20define%20what%20services%20they%20would%20be%20permitted%20to%20offer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20most%20well-known%20private%20armies%20in%20the%20region%2C%20Russia's%20Wagner%20Group%2C%20fought%20alongside%20the%20Kremlin's%20troops%20against%20Ukraine%20during%20the%20earlier%20years%20of%20the%20war.%20The%20contractor%20firm%20is%20often%20considered%20a%20shadow%20extension%20of%20Moscow's%20military%2C%20but%20has%20fallen%20in%20influence%20after%20its%20then-leader%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwho-is-yevgeny-prigozhin-russian-tycoon-and-vladimir-putin-confidant-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EYevgeny%20Prigozhin%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20notoriously%20launched%20a%20dramatic%2C%20short-lived%20coup%20in%202023%20.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-private-military-company-legalize-zelenskyy-postwar-jobs-2026-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1778142489000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69fc3d03e1443b8dc48e2a8e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-private-military-company-legalize-zelenskyy-postwar-jobs-2026-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Zelenskyy%20is%20seeking%20to%20legalize%20private%20military%20firms%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20potentially%20giving%20the%20country's%20some%20900%2C000%20troops%20postwar%20career%20opportunities.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22mloh%40businessinsider.com%20(Matthew%20Loh)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ford%20CEO%20says%20the%20US%20is%20'the%20most%20vulnerable%20we've%20ever%20been'%20amid%20worker%20shortages%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jim%20Farley%2C%20Ford's%20CEO%2C%20lifts%20his%20left%20hand%20while%20speaking%20onstage.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69fb9357c9dd4cb81cda7cd0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJim%20Farley%20has%20been%20focusing%20on%20the%20US's%20shortage%20of%20%26quot%3Btktk%26quot%3B%20workers%3Cp%3EBloomberg%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EFord's%20CEO%20continued%20his%20warning%20about%20a%20skilled%20workers%20shortage%20in%20the%20US%20in%20a%20coming%20podcast.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHis%20guest%20added%2C%20%26quot%3BPeople%20don't%20care%20about%20a%20shortage%20of%20plumbers%20until%20their%20toilet%20doesn't%20flush.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENearly%20half%20of%20manufacturers%20say%20hiring%20is%20a%20top%20challenge%2C%20industry%20data%20shows.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fford-ceo-jim-farley-xiaomi-tesla-chinese-ev-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EFord%20CEO%20Jim%20Farley%3C%2Fa%3E%20says%20the%20US%20is%20in%20a%20%26quot%3Breally%20vulnerable%20place%26quot%3B%20due%20to%20ongoing%20skilled%20worker%20shortages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20would%20argue%20the%20most%20vulnerable%20we've%20ever%20been%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20in%20a%20new%20episode%20of%20his%20podcast%2C%20%26quot%3BDrive.%26quot%3B%20The%20automaker%20shared%20a%20transcript%20ahead%20of%20the%20episode's%20Friday%20release%20with%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20past%20year%2C%20the%20Detroit%20automaker's%20top%20boss%20has%20publicly%20raised%20concerns%20about%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fford-ceo-wanted-his-son-to-learn-to-weld-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eshortage%20of%20skilled%20workers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20construction%20workers%2C%20manufacturing%20employees%2C%20and%20tradespeople.%20Farley%20has%20referred%20to%20this%20segment%20of%20the%20workforce%20as%20the%20%26quot%3Bessential%20economy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIndustry%20data%20reflects%20similar%20concerns.%20Nearly%20half%20of%20US%20manufacturers%20say%20attracting%20and%20retaining%20workers%20is%20a%20top%20challenge%2C%20according%20to%20the%20National%20Association%20of%20Manufacturers'%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnam.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsecurepdfs%2F2026%2F03%2FNAM_Q1_2026_Outlook_Write_Up.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elatest%20quarterly%20survey%3C%2Fa%3E.%20A%202023%20study%20cited%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.census.gov%2Flibrary%2Fstories%2F2023%2F09%2Fmanufacturing-faces-labor-shortage.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS%20Census%20Bureau%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20the%20US%20could%20face%202.1%20million%20unfilled%20manufacturing%20jobs%20by%202030.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFarley%20said%20the%20impact%20of%20those%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Folder-americans-taking-blue-collar-jobs-white-collar-hiring-slowdown-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eblue-collar%20shortages%3C%2Fa%3E%20could%20ripple%20across%20the%20broader%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BProblems%20in%20this%20vital%20sector%20impact%20all%20of%20us%20with%20higher%20costs%2C%20longer%20wait%20times%2C%20and%20fewer%20opportunities%2C%26quot%3B%20Farley%20said%20on%20the%20podcast.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20guest%2C%20Mike%20Rowe%2C%20the%20host%20of%20the%20television%20series%20%26quot%3BDirty%20Jobs%2C%26quot%3B%20agreed%3A%20%26quot%3BThose%20people%20don't%20care%20about%20a%20shortage%20of%20plumbers%20until%20their%20toilet%20doesn't%20flush.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFord%20and%20Farley%20have%20been%20trying%20to%20attract%20more%20talent%20over%20the%20past%20year.%20In%20January%2C%20the%20company%20told%20Business%20Insider%20about%20plans%20to%20attract%20new%20workers%2C%20including%20offering%20incentives%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fford-mechanics-free-carhartt-auto-tech-scholars-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efree%20Carhartt%20gear%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20to%20invest%20in%20a%20Detroit-based%20ToolBank%20USA%20location.%20In%20September%2C%20the%20company%20organized%20a%20workforce%20development%20summit%20that%20convened%20industry%20leaders%20and%20policymakers%20to%20address%20the%20trades%20pipeline%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20stopped%20investing%20in%20the%20trades%2C%26quot%3B%20Farley%20said%20at%20the%20September%20event.%20%26quot%3BIf%20Henry%20Ford%20saw%20what%20has%20become%20of%20us%2C%20I%20think%20he'd%20be%20kind%20of%20mad.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFord%20is%20not%20alone.%20Rival%20Detroit%20automaker%20General%20Motors%20told%20Business%20Insider%20it%20has%20invested%20nearly%20%24200%20million%20over%20the%20past%20year%20to%20expand%20training%20programs%20and%20apprenticeships%20to%20grow%20its%20workforce.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fford-ceo-jim-farley-worker-shortage-manufacturing-2026-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1778142181000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69fbbe1ac9dd4cb81cda7e8a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fford-ceo-jim-farley-worker-shortage-manufacturing-2026-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Ford%20CEO%20Jim%20Farley%20warns%20again%20about%20worker%20shortages%20that%20could%20strain%20manufacturing%20and%20the%20economy.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22bshimkus%40insider.com%20(Ben%20Shimkus)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20haven't%20worn%20my%20wedding%20ring%20in%207%20years.%20It%20doesn't%20mean%20my%20marriage%20is%20on%20the%20rocks.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223117%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20author%20and%20her%20husband.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69f8d4a3ab24bc0b23a190fb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222338%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20hasn't%20worn%20her%20wedding%20ring%20in%20years%2C%20but%20it's%20not%20a%20reflection%20of%20the%20status%20of%20her%20relationship.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Sara%20Rowe%20Mount%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EInitially%2C%20wearing%20a%20wedding%20ring%20was%20something%20that%20I%20was%20happy%20and%20proud%20to%20do.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EChanges%20to%20my%20body%20during%20and%20after%20pregnancy%20resulted%20in%20my%20wedding%20ring%20not%20fitting%20anymore.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAfter%20not%20being%20able%20to%20wear%20it%20for%20a%20while%2C%20I've%20realized%20it's%20not%20something%20I%20value%20anymore.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EGrowing%20up%20in%20conservative%20circles%2C%20marriage%20felt%20like%20a%20foregone%20conclusion.%20It%20was%20a%20life%20stage%20everyone%20participated%20in%2C%20like%20starting%20a%20career%20or%20having%20children.%20I%20was%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsigns-youll-be-a-late-bloomer-career-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elate%20bloomer%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20I%20didn't%20even%20date%20until%20after%20college.%20Many%20of%20my%20peers%20had%20gotten%20married%20in%20their%20early%2020s%2C%20while%20I%20was%20playing%20catch-up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20felt%20like%20being%20married%20was%20fully%20'adulting%2C'%20and%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhusband-wife-dont-wear-wedding-rings-dont-like-jewelry-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewedding%20ring%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20almost%20a%20status%20symbol.%20Being%20single%20made%20me%20feel%20less%20than.%20So%20early%20on%20in%20my%20marriage%2C%20I%20was%20happy%20(and%20honestly%2C%20almost%20relieved)%20when%20looking%20at%20my%20rings%2C%20knowing%20that%20someone%20loved%20me%20enough%20to%20commit%20to%20life%20with%20me.%20But%20for%20the%20last%20seven%20years%20%E2%80%94%20the%20majority%20of%20my%20marriage%20%E2%80%94%20I%20actually%20haven't%20worn%20them%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22cbeba213-be79-4da7-8632-7c652eb43549%5C%22%3EI%20first%20stopped%20wearing%20my%20rings%20because%20I%20had%20to%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20few%20years%20into%20my%20marriage%2C%20I%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freference%2Fhow-to-get-pregnant%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egot%20pregnant%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20my%20daughter%2C%20and%20my%20body%20began%20to%20change.%20In%20later%20pregnancy%2C%20my%20rings%20started%20to%20get%20snug%20as%20my%20fingers%20swelled%2C%20and%20I%20was%20afraid%20that%20one%20day%20I%20wouldn't%20be%20able%20to%20get%20them%20off%20and%20on%20anymore.%20So%20they%20got%20put%20away%20for%20the%20duration%20of%20my%20pregnancy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20the%20time%20period%20when%20I%20got%20the%20most%20questions%20from%20family%20members%20about%20where%20my%20rings%20were.%20They%20seemed%20to%20be%20concerned%20that%20strangers%20might%20think%20that%20I%20was%20pregnant%20and%20unmarried.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcouple-had-four-daughters-born-on-same-birthday-by-coincidence-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edaughter%20was%20born%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20rings%20fit%20again%2C%20and%20I%20returned%20to%20wearing%20them.%20But%20then%20I%20gained%20some%20weight%2C%20and%20they%20began%20to%20feel%20snug%20again.%20I%20put%20them%20away%20in%20my%20jewelry%20box%20with%20the%20thought%20that%20once%20I%20lost%20weight%2C%20I'd%20be%20able%20to%20wear%20them%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22702bde16-4e75-402c-b76a-2ac96a812343%5C%22%3EThe%20rings%20weren't%20as%20important%20to%20me%20anymore%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20years%20passed.%20After%20losing%20some%20weight%2C%20I%20tried%20them%20on%20again%2C%20and%20they%20still%20didn't%20fit.%20And%20while%20I've%20been%20thinking%20about%20getting%20them%20resized%20for%20probably%20two%20years%20now%2C%20I%20still%20haven't%20gotten%20around%20to%20it.%20There's%20really%20no%20deeper%20meaning%20to%20it.%20It%20isn't%20a%20reflection%20of%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsigns-of-strong-marriage-couples-therapist-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emarriage's%20health%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20of%20how%20I%20feel%20about%20my%20husband.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20others%20might%20feel%20that%20wearing%20a%20wedding%20ring%20is%20a%20symbol%20of%20commitment%2C%20to%20me%2C%20it's%20always%20felt%20more%20about%20the%20people%20outside%20your%20marriage.%20I%20don't%20feel%20like%20I%20need%20an%20outward%20signal%20to%20others%20that%20I'm%20married%2C%20nor%20do%20I%20really%20care%20as%20much%20about%20what%20others%20think%20about%20me%20or%20my%20marriage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20choice%20not%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstopped-wearing-wedding-rings-nonmonogamous-polyamorous-relationship-marriage-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewear%20a%20wedding%20ring%3C%2Fa%3E%20wasn't%20the%20only%20thing%20that%20some%20family%20members%20and%20friends%20were%20critical%20of%2C%20though.%20Since%20we've%20distanced%20ourselves%20from%20a%20lot%20of%20these%20more%20conservative%20(and%20frankly%20judgmental)%20people%20and%20made%20new%20friends%2C%20I%20haven't%20gotten%20any%20comments%20on%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20my%20husband%20is%20unbothered%20that%20I%20don't%20wear%20my%20wedding%20ring%2C%20he%20still%20wears%20his%20because%20it%20is%20meaningful%20to%20him.%20He%20even%20has%20a%20silicon%20ring%20that%20he%20wears%20when%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyouth-sports-expensive-competitive-huge-commitment-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eplaying%20rec%20sports%3C%2Fa%3E.%20He%20thinks%20it%20should%20be%20a%20personal%20choice%2C%20rather%20than%20an%20obligation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20still%20might%20get%20my%20rings%20resized%20in%20the%20future%20and%20start%20to%20wear%20them%20again.%20But%20it%20will%20be%20because%20I%20want%20to%2C%20not%20because%20it's%20something%20that's%20expected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdont-wear-wedding-ring-marriage-is-great-2026-5%5C%22%3EBusin