ormat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223712%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20XRQ-73%20flew%20in%20April%20in%20California%2C%20DARPA%20said.%3Cp%3EDARPA%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAn%20experimental%20US%20tactical%20stealth%20drone%20called%20the%20XRQ-73%20just%20took%20flight%20in%20California.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20US%20military%20said%20the%20stealth%20drone%20mixes%20electric%20and%20jet%20fuel%20propulsion%20for%20better%20efficiency.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20drone%20is%20shaped%20like%20other%20stealth%20aircraft%2C%20such%20as%20the%20B-2%20Spirit%20and%20the%20RQ-170%20Sentinel.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20military's%20defense%20tech%20agency%20said%20on%20Wednesday%20that%20it%20flew%20an%20experimental%20hybrid-electric%20drone%20called%20the%20XRQ-73%2C%20testing%20a%20next-gen%20propulsion%20system%20for%20longer%2C%20quieter%20flight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20drone%2C%20built%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnorthrop-grumman-taking-financial-hit-b21-raider-stealth-bomber-us-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ENorthrop%20Grumman%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20flew%20at%20Edwards%20Air%20Force%20Base%20in%20California%20in%20April%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdarpa-wants-cheaper-missiles-as-us-burns-through-stockpiles-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EDefense%20Advanced%20Research%20Projects%20Agency%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20tech%20uses%20a%20mix%20of%20electric%20and%20jet-fuel%20propulsion%2C%20which%20is%20meant%20to%20help%20the%20drone%20burn%20less%20fuel%20and%20reduce%20emissions%20for%20better%20stealth.%20Most%20medium-%20to%20long-range%20military%20drones%20use%20jet%20engines%20or%20propellers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20milestone%20is%20not%20just%20about%20a%20single%20flight%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Lt.%20Col.%20Clark%20McGehee%2C%20the%20program's%20manager.%20%26quot%3BThe%20architecture%20proven%20by%20the%20XRQ-73%20paves%20the%20way%20for%20new%20types%20of%20mission%20systems%20and%20delivered%20effects.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225568%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20XRQ-73%20sits%20on%20the%20desert.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69fbfed1c9dd4cb81cda7f23%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223712%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20XRQ-73%20appears%20to%20feature%20a%20stabilizing%20winglet%20on%20each%20side.%3Cp%3EDARPA%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPhotos%20of%20the%20XRQ-73%20show%20that%20its%20exterior%20design%20loosely%20resembles%20that%20of%20other%20stealth%20aircraft%2C%20such%20as%20Northrop%20Grumman's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-us-air-force-is-keeping-b2-spirit-bombers-lethal-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EB-2%20Spirit%20bomber%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20Lockheed%20Martin's%20RQ-170%20Sentinel%20drone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20those%20aircraft%2C%20however%2C%20the%20tailless%20XRQ-73%20features%20winglets%20at%20the%20ends%20of%20each%20wing.%20A%20front-facing%20camera%20is%20also%20visible%20near%20the%20XRQ-73's%20nose.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20unclear%20how%20quickly%20the%20US%20plans%20to%20move%20forward%20with%20the%20XRQ-73.%20DARPA%20has%20said%20that%20the%20drone's%20program%20is%20designed%20to%20%26quot%3Bprovide%20a%20minimum%20viable%20product%20to%20meet%20an%20urgent%20operational%20need.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20agency%20also%20said%20in%202024%20that%20it%20had%20expected%20the%20XRQ-73's%20first%20flight%20to%20occur%20at%20the%20end%20of%20that%20year%2C%20indicating%20that%20the%20drone's%20development%20was%20delayed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20XRQ-73%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-built-out-base-new-jet-powered-drones-satellite-images-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ea%20Group-3%20drone%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20intended%20as%20a%20medium-sized%20tactical%20system%20that%20flies%20below%2018%2C000%20feet%20and%20at%20speeds%20between%20115%20and%20287%20mph.%20DARPA%20said%20it%20weighs%20about%201%2C250%20pounds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIts%20program%20is%20part%20of%20a%20contract%20from%20the%20Air%20Force%20Research%20Laboratory%20called%20the%20Great%20Horned%20Owl%2C%20which%20aims%20to%20develop%20an%20efficient%2C%20ultra-stealthy%20recon%20drone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20similarly%20designed%20but%20smaller%2C%20earlier%20version%20of%20the%20XRQ-73%2C%20called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.twz.com%2F32807%2Fexclusive-unmasking-northrop-grummans-xrq-72a-great-horned-owl-spy-drone%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20XRQ-72A%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20was%20in%20the%20works%20since%20at%20least%202010.%20But%20it's%20unclear%20if%20it%20ever%20flew.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20contacted%2C%20Northrop%20Grumman%20pointed%20Business%20Insider%20to%20DARPA%2C%20which%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20sent%20outside%20regular%20business%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-military-flew-experimental-hybrid-stealth-drone-xrq-73-2026-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1778126745000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69fc08d03cfefc31768d671a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-military-flew-experimental-hybrid-stealth-drone-xrq-73-2026-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20XRQ-73%2C%20a%201%2C250-pound%20drone%2C%20uses%20a%20mix%20of%20electric%20and%20jet-fuel%20propulsion%2C%20which%20is%20supposed%20to%20make%20it%20much%20quieter%20and%20fly%20more%20efficiently.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22mloh%40businessinsider.com%20(Matthew%20Loh)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A97%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Mark%20Cuban%20says%20you%20should%20ask%205%20questions%20about%20your%20company%20and%20its%20leadership%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Mark%20Cuban%20at%20the%202026%20SXSW%20Conference%20And%20Festival%20at%20JW%20Marriott%20Austin%20on%20March%2014%2C%202026%2C%20in%20Austin.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69bd1d9aebc245a53a8122a7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224796%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMark%20Cuban%20said%20there%20are%20five%20questions%20employees%20should%20ask%20about%20their%20company%20when%20deciding%20whether%20to%20stay%20or%20leave.%3Cp%3ENicola%20Gell%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EMark%20Cuban%20has%20a%20five-question%20guide%20to%20assessing%20a%20company's%20health%20in%20the%20age%20of%20AI.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20said%20that%20if%20your%20CEO%20doesn't%20understand%20AI%2C%20%26quot%3Bstart%20to%20think%20about%20another%20job.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EChecking%20if%20your%20company%20is%20growing%20and%20if%20you%20feel%20intellectually%20challenged%20is%20also%20important%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EMark%20Cuban%20is%20back%20with%20more%20career%20advice%20in%20the%20age%20of%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20Wednesday%20X%20post%2C%20the%20billionaire%20former%20%26quot%3BShark%20Tank%26quot%3B%20investor%20listed%20out%20five%20things%20that%20employees%20should%20take%20note%20of%20before%20deciding%20whether%20to%20stay%20put%20or%20leave%20for%20another%20company%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EIs%20your%20company%20growing%3F%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAs%20an%20employee%2C%20what%20is%20it%20that%20you%20do%20and%20can%20do%20in%20the%20future%2C%20to%20better%20contribute%20to%20those%20profits%2Fgoals%3F%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAre%20you%20intellectually%20challenged%20in%20your%20job%3F%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAre%20you%20spending%20as%20much%20time%20as%20you%20can%20find%20to%20learn%20all%20you%20can%20about%20AI%3F%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EDoes%20your%20CEO%20understand%20AI%3F%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EExpanding%20on%20the%20fifth%20question%2C%20Cuban%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BIf%20the%20CEO%20has%20no%20clue%2C%20start%20to%20think%20about%20another%20job.%20Your%20company%20is%20going%20to%20be%20challenged%20over%20the%20next%20few%20years.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20talked%20about%20the%20importance%20of%20being%20AI-literate.%20He%20said%20that%20if%20the%20company%20is%20growing%20and%20employees%20feel%20intellectually%20challenged%20in%20their%20roles%2C%20they%20can%20use%20AI%20to%20contribute%20to%20that%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20company%20will%20need%20as%20many%20people%20like%20you%20as%20it%20can%20get.%20It%20has%20a%20really%20good%20chance%20to%20outperform%20its%20competitors%2C%20because%20it%20has%20an%20AI%20literate%20workforce%2C%26quot%3B%20Cuban%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20AI%20is%20not%20easy%20to%20implement%20and%20is%20not%20a%20%26quot%3Bsilver%20bullet%20that%20guarantees%20success%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20rather%20a%20tool%20that%20can%20help%20%26quot%3Bsmart%20people%20make%20smarter%20decisions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20not%20the%20first%20time%20Cuban%20has%20given%20career%20advice%20to%20workers%20on%20how%20to%20get%20ahead%20with%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20December%2C%20he%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmark-cuban-new-grads-small-businesses-ai-agents-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Enew%20graduates%3C%2Fa%3E%20should%20opt%20for%20working%20in%20small-%20to%20medium-sized%20businesses%2C%20where%20they%20could%20lead%20the%20deployment%20of%20AI%20agents%2C%20rather%20than%20big%20companies%20that%20don't%20need%20that%20skill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20in%20April%2C%20he%20gave%20practical%20advice%20on%20which%20prompts%20to%20feed%20into%20Claude%20to%20sharpen%20skills.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmark-cuban-future-proof-career-ai-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%